[1]
Date: Mon 26 Dec 2011
Source: Notosistema, Guadalajara, Mexico [in Spanish, machine transl.,
edited]
http://www.notisistema.com/noticias/?p=452275


Mass poisoning leaves 6 people dead and 34 injured in the Jara,
Creator of Life hostel for alcoholics and [drug] addicts. The center
is located in Federation Street at the intersection with Mariano
Jimenez in Colonia La Perla, Guadalajara, Jalisco. Among those
affected are 2 doctors and a Red Cross paramedic who treated 2 of the
dead, by the toxic gases emitted by the bodies, which were evacuated
at the aid station at Parque Morelos. The victims ate vegetables, rice
and sausage that allegedly contained cyanide.

[Byline: Juan Carlos Huerta Vasquez]

